Certainly! Here's a simple "Hello, World!" program in C:

```c
#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    /* my first program in C */
    printf("Hello World! \n");
    return 0;
}
```

You can save this code in a file named `hello.c`, compile it with a C compiler like gcc, and then run the executable to see the output. For example, on a command line:

```bash
gcc hello.c -o hello
./hello
```

This will display:

```
Hello World!
```

(Source: [TutorialsPoint - C Hello World](https://www.tutorialspoint.com/cprogramming/c_hello_world.htm))
